golden_answer:
This is a known issue after upograding to 12.2.1.2. Apply the provided drop file with these steps if you are on version 12.2.1.2:
1. Upload the attached drop files(dcm-py3.pyc, dcm-py2,pyc) into “/home/em7admin/” directory across all database appliances on the stack.
2. Backup the existing dcm.pyc files in both Python 2 and Python 3 locations, to new filenames:
cp -p /opt/em7/lib/python/sl_da_storageobj/dcm.pyc /opt/em7/lib/python/sl_da_storageobj/dcm.pyc.orig;
cp -p /opt/em7/lib/python3/sl_da_storageobj/dcm.pyc /opt/em7/lib/python3/sl_da_storageobj/dcm.pyc.orig;
3. Copy the new dcm-py2.pyc file to /opt/em7/lib/python/sl_da_storageobj, removing the ‘-py2’ portion of the filename. Then set the ownership of the file to root:s-em7-srv and set its permissions to 640.
chmod 640 /home/em7admin/dcm-py2.pyc;
chown root:s-em7-srv /home/em7admin/dcm-py2.pyc;
cp -p /home/em7admin/dcm-py2.pyc /opt/em7/lib/python/sl_da_storageobj/dcm.pyc;
When asked if you want to replace the file, pick “yes”.
4. Copy the new dcm-py3.pyc file to /opt/em7/lib/python3/sl_da_storageobj, removing the ‘-py3’ portion of the filename. Then set the ownership of the file to root:root and set its permissions to 744.
chmod 744 /home/em7admin/dcm-py3.pyc;
chown root:root /home/em7admin/dcm-py3.pyc;
cp -p /home/em7admin/dcm-py3.pyc /opt/em7/lib/python3/sl_da_storageobj/dcm.pyc;
When asked if you want to replace the file, pick “yes”.
5. Only on Primary Database appliance. Restart the three Data Pull services with command:
sudo systemctl restart em7_hfpulld em7_mfpulld em7_lfpulld
6. Check MySQL processlist(System>Tools>DB Tool and run "SHOW FULL PROCESSLIST" query), and notice that you don’t see queries like this taking over 1-2 seconds to complete:
SELECT cdm.id, cdm.parent_did, cdm.root_did, cdm.component_did, cdm.unique_id, ld.cug_id, (scg.fake_cug_capacity != 0) AS in_virtual_cug, ld.id AS did, ld.class_type, ld.keep_hostname, ld.device AS device_name, FALSE as vanished FROM master_dev.component_dev_map cdm JOIN master_dev.legend_device ld ON ld.id = cdm.component_did JOIN master.system_collector_groups scg ON scg.cug_id = ld.cug_id WHERE IF(guid IS NOT NULL, guid = 'xxxxxxxxxx', unique_id in ('xxxxxxxxxx') AND root_did = 12345)
7. Check your devices, and make sure performance graph data is pulled and populated for the next 15-20 minutes. Also check if Rows Behind number is going down on the monitored primary DB device.
Issue is also fixed in 12.2.3 and 12.3.0.
